oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of the U.S.S. Nadawaska
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Ruby Glenn Blevins of Blount County returned from England in 1919 on the U.S.S. Nadawaska. The ship is painted in a dazzle pattern camofluage. Blevins served in Co. L, 117th Inf. Regt., 30th Div. during World War I. Blevins was wounded slightly in action on September 24, 1918, and survived the war. The family reports that he refused promotion and died in 1971.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
